<subSubSection id="121D6F3675ACF7DAA6593560D956A44A" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="6D708B75DBF36C6735211AFA4E5252FB" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9722B98C268E008AAE8832376D230ED0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
The generic name is a combination of Greek, micro (
<normalizedToken id="392CBE4BEF4A2CCBC0F139FF26D9BAF9" originalValue="mikrós">mikros</normalizedToken>
) = small, related to the small size of the adult type-specimen, and 
<taxonomicName id="03475B8C038C3DFB950867394752430D" lsidName="plecostomus" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" rank="species" species="plecostomus">plecostomus</taxonomicName>
= a former generic name of species currently included in 
<taxonomicName id="DA347D0EF97CFAB31249F9451AAF5D2D" family="Loricariidae" lsidName="" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" rank="family">Loricariidae</taxonomicName>
, also in reference to the small adult size of the type-species. A masculine name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
